<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-09-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-09-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="207" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d207">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. F. W. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Dayton</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 668.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-09-26"><hi rend="italic">September</hi> 26, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your despatch of the 9th
                            instant, No. 536, which reates to the confederate ships now being built
                            at Bordeaux and Nantes, which <pb facs="0170" n="150" xml:id="pg_150"/>
                            is approved. I am pleased to see that you have anticipated and fully
                            executed the instructions contained in a despatch of the 8th of August,
                            No. 629.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>F. W. SEWARD, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">William L. Dayton,</hi>
                                <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>